
Trinket
===================
NJR(NanJi Repository) is the next generation PHP library for developing web applications.

"NJ" is a code name for this project,since "Nan Ji" where we work at.


PHP Dependencies
===================
__Version:__

 * PHP 5+

__Modules:__

 * [memcached](http://pecl.php.net/package/memcached)
 * [pcre](http://php.net/manual/en/book.pcre.php)
 * [curl](http://php.net/manual/en/book.curl.php)
 * [PDO](http://php.net/manual/en/book.pdo.php)
 * [APC](http://php.net/manual/en/book.apc.php) *recommended but not required.*
 

Installing Locally
==================
_Note that this install currently requires read/write permission at /usr/share/ where NJR will be put under.
* `sudo make install`


After Install
==================
* Define NJR path like this:
  <code>defined('NJR') or define('NJR','/usr/share/NJR/');</code>

* Import NJR lib in your code as follows:
  <code>require("/usr/share/NJR/NJ.php");</code>

* Load and run NJ_XXX as you wish.


